headline: Down 61% From Its All-Time High, Could This Beaten-Down Dividend King Stock Finally Turn the Corner in 2025?
summary: Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE: SWK) is a tool-maker titan.  It owns well-known brands DeWalt, Craftsman, Irwin, and LENOX, and, of course, Stanley and Black & Decker.  The sell-off may come as a surprise, since Stanley Black & Decker is a Dividend King with a 3.9% yield and 56 consecutive years of dividend raises.
